It is a meditation for the body. I was always thin, and always enjoyed sprinting and various exercises, because of how amazing it makes you feel. It's not just about losing weight. This argument is as ridiculous as saying that a muscular man can't get some weights as a gift, just because he's already muscular. It's ridiculous. And perhaps the woman in that commercial was thin only because she goes to the gym 2 or 3 times per week. But now she can exercise at her home, and spend more time with her daughter. Everyone needs to just relax and stop being so butt-hurt and whiny about everything, and stop looking at everything so negatively.
